      Returns:
      the new value associated with the key, either as a result of applying function to the value already associated with the key or as a result of applying it to initialValueIfAbsent and associating the result with key

      MutableByteShortMap asUnmodifiable()
      Returns an unmodifiable view of this map, delegating all read-only operations to this map and throwing an UnsupportedOperationException for all mutating operations. This avoids the overhead of copying the map when calling ByteShortMap.toImmutable() while still providing immutability.
